column5: Here are a couple more videos from the weekend that I got as well as my neighbour he got his first casting musky that was 50.25" that was cool but the tail and lower fin were messed up bad. I also got a 50" that morning and 5 others but will post that later have not had time to do the video. Please feel free to share my videos and check out the other ones on You Tube      here is his fish     My 46" from the night before   also some cool sun set pics of the boats racing across LSC
Mike been reading your reports,you sure have them dialed in.Can't wait for your next report!!!Nice fish!  .
Great show Mike!  Two things, capturing the muskie takes and, clipping onto the net.  That's a great idea.  You've had a solid month at least.

Thanks Davey  Yes Andrew it's a repeat of last fall I'm glad to see the years of work pay off its nice to have a plan and work it well. I'm just glad that the musky also want to eat.  One thing people fishing musky need to remember is change up things until you find out what they want. Pay attention to the little things to repeat good days.
Nice fish Mike!! Looking forward to fishing LSC next week.
Thanks Phil Im looking forward to this fall with you guys  See you this weekend Pete
As always mike great report and great video. Keep it up !
